<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="532" pageId="1" pageNumber="530" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[813,1451,1742,1913]" lastBlockId="3.[128,765,138,190]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="532" pageId="1" pageNumber="530">Diagnosis.—Anterolateral spine of carapace short, not reaching base of cornea; protogastric and epigastric lobes absent; extra-orbital sinus absent, rostrum triangular, deflected, carinate, outer proximal margin of movable finger of cheliped with lobe; palmar crest of cheliped subdisciform; anterior angle of ventral margin of epimeron 2 with modest scales; inner marginof ventral surface of ischium of cheliped with distal scaliform tubercle.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3562859" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3562859" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3562859/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="531" startId="2.[137,168,1840,1859]" targetBox="[180,1415,129,1814]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[137,1459,1840,1883]" pageId="2" pageNumber="531">
